# Implementation of `instrument_call_statement`

The function is located at lines 1041-1080 in the source file. Here's what triggers heap allocation/deallocation tracking:

## Function Name Comparisons

The implementation checks the callee's identifier against exactly two strings:

1. **"malloc"** (line 1053): When this function is called and has an assignment to an LHS, the code extracts the returned pointer and calls `track_heap_allocated`:

```
if(callee_name == "malloc")
{
  const auto &function_call = to_code_function_call(instruction_it->code());
  if(function_call.lhs().is_not_nil())
  {
    auto object = pointer_object(function_call.lhs());
    // ... track_heap_allocated(object, payload);
  }
}
```

2. **"free"** (line 1072): When this function is called, the code extracts the pointer argument and calls `check_inclusion_heap_allocated_and_invalidate_aliases`:

```
else if(callee_name == "free")
{
  const auto &ptr = instruction_it->call_arguments().front();
  auto object = pointer_object(ptr);
  // ... check_inclusion_heap_allocated_and_invalidate_aliases(object, payload);
}
```

